# Dallah Admin Dashboard — Frontend Integration Guide

**Base URL:** `http://<server>:31000`  
**All endpoints:** `POST/GET/PATCH/DELETE /api/v1/dallah/...`  
**Content-Type:** `application/json`  

---

## Authentication Overview

The API supports two auth methods. The frontend always uses **JWT**.

Every request (except `POST /auth/login`) must include:
```
Authorization: Bearer <token>
```

If the token is missing, expired, or invalid → **401 Unauthorized**.

---

## 1. Auth Endpoints

### Login
```
POST /api/v1/dallah/auth/login
```
**Public — no Authorization header needed.**

Request body:
```json
{
  "email": "ksaleh@aanaab.com",
  "password": "Dallah@2026!"
}
```

Success `200`:
```json
{
  "token": "eyJhbGci...",
  "admin": {
    "id": 1,
    "name": "K Saleh",
    "email": "ksaleh@aanaab.com",
    "role": "super_admin"
  }
}
```

Error `401`:
```json
{ "error": "Invalid email or password" }
```

**Store the token** in `localStorage` or a secure cookie. Attach it to every subsequent request.

---

### Get Current Admin Profile
```
GET /api/v1/dallah/auth/me
```
**Requires JWT only** (static M2M bearer will be rejected here).

Success `200`:
```json
{
  "admin": {
    "id": 1,
    "name": "K Saleh",
    "email": "ksaleh@aanaab.com",
    "role": "super_admin"
  }
}
```

Use this on app load to validate the stored token and get the current user's role.

