## 4. User Endpoints

### Search / List Users
```
GET /api/v1/dallah/users?q=<search_term>
```
- Search by **name** or **mobile number**: partial match (e.g. `?q=ahmed`)
- Search by **national ID**: must be exact 10-digit match starting with 1 or 2 (e.g. `?q=1234567890`)
- Omit `q` to get the 50 most recent users

Response `200`:
```json
{
  "users": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "name": "Ahmed Ali",
      "national_id": "1234567890",
      "mobile_number": "+966501234567",
      "email": "ahmed@dallah.edu.sa",
      "lang": "ar",
      "status": "created",
      "organization_branch_id": 1,
      "enrollments": [
        {
          "id": 5,
          "status": "created",
          "course": {
            "id": 1,
            "course_name": "Private Driving - Arabic",
            "dallah_course_code": "P6h",
            "language": "Arabic",
            "category": "private"
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

### Create Single User + Enroll
```
POST /api/v1/dallah/users
```
Request body:
```json
{
  "national_id": "1234567890",
  "name": "Ahmed Ali",
  "mobile": "+966501234567",
  "lang": "1",
  "school_id": 6,
  "courses": [
    {
      "dallah_course_code": "P6h",
      "licence_type": "private",
      "lang": "1"
    }
  ]
}
```

- `lang`: get the numeric code from `GET /languages` (e.g. `"1"` = Arabic)
- `school_id`: use the `dallah_school_id` (1–10) from the branch table above
- `dallah_course_code`: get from `GET /courses`
- `licence_type`: `"private"`, `"motor"`, or `"public"`

Success `200` — returns created user data.
Error `422` — returns `{ "error": "...", "details": [...] }`.

### Bulk Create Users (JSON)
```
POST /api/v1/dallah/users/bulk
```
Request body:
```json
{
  "users": [
    {
      "national_id": "1234567890",
      "name": "Ahmed Ali",
      "mobile": "+966501234567",
      "lang": "1",
      "school_id": 6,
      "courses": [{ "dallah_course_code": "P6h", "licence_type": "private", "lang": "1" }]
    }
  ]
}
```
Max 100 users per request. Response includes per-user success/failure breakdown.

### Bulk Create Users (CSV Upload)

#### Download CSV Template
```
GET /api/v1/dallah/users/bulk_csv/template
```
Returns a downloadable `.csv` file with the correct headers and one example row. Show a "Download Template" button in the UI before the upload form.

#### Upload CSV File
```
POST /api/v1/dallah/users/bulk_csv
Content-Type: multipart/form-data
```
Form field: `file` → attach the CSV file.

**CSV columns (all required):**

| Column | Description | Example |
|---|---|---|
| `name` | Full name | Ahmed Ali |
| `national_id` | 10-digit Saudi ID starting with 1 or 2 | 1234567890 |
| `mobile` | Saudi mobile with country code | +966501234567 |
| `lang` | Language code from `GET /languages` | 1 |
| `school_id` | Branch `dallah_school_id` (1–10) | 6 |
| `dallah_course_code` | Course code from `GET /courses` | P6h |
| `licence_type` | `private`, `motor`, or `public` | private |

Each row = one user + one course enrollment. Max 100 rows per upload.

Success `200`:
```json
{
  "message": "Bulk user enrollment processed",
  "summary": { "total": 3, "successful": 2, "failed": 1 },
  "results": [ { "national_id": "1234567890", "aanaab_user_id": 123, ... } ],
  "failed_users": [
    { "national_id": "9999999999", "errors": ["User national id or mobile number conflicts with existing users"] }
  ]
}
```
Always check `failed_users` — valid rows are processed even when some rows fail.

### Update User
```
PATCH /api/v1/dallah/users
```
Request body:
```json
{
  "current_national_id": "1234567890",
  "name": "Ahmed Ali Updated",
  "mobile": "+966509999999",
  "lang": "2"
}
```
`current_national_id` is required to find the user. All other fields are optional.

